## 4. Data-Ink and Graphical Redesign

*data-ink* - the non-erasable core of a graphic, the non-redundant ink arranged in response to variation in the numbers represented.


```javascript
const data-ink ratio = data-ink / total ink used to print the graphic
```


*Erasing Principles*

- erase *non-data-ink*, within reason
- erase *redundant data-ink*


*Conclusion*

- above all else show the data
- maximize the data-ink ratio
- erase non-data-ink
- erase redundant data-ink
- revise and edita
